{
  "text": "and A 2 (z) ∈ R m×p has no special form. Thereby, the elements of the strictly lower triangular part of (10) and of A 2 (z) are determined by the kernel (see Appendix 4 for details). Using the method of characteristics, the boundary value problem (BVP) (8) can be converted into integral equations. The latter is solvable by means of a fixpoint iteration. This allows to show that a unique piecewise (8) exists (see [CITATION_1] . Hence, the kernel is attainable by utilising a successive approximation. Further details for solving (8) are provided in Appendix 4.",
